From: walbrix infra <shimada@walbrix.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 18:30:00 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] application: fall back to GLibUnix.signal_add with GLib >= 2.80

With dev-libs/glib >= 2.80 the Unix-specific introspection API
(g_unix_signal_add etc.) was moved out of the GLib-2.0 namespace into
GLibUnix-2.0. On systems where GLib.unix_signal_add is no longer
available (observed with glib-2.88.1 + pygobject-3.50.1), the
native messaging host raises AttributeError during Application.__init__
and exits immediately, which the browser reports as
"Native host has exited."

Try the old API first and fall back to GLibUnix.signal_add.

--- a/gnome_browser_connector/application.py	2022-09-07 17:03:51.000000000 +0900
+++ b/gnome_browser_connector/application.py	2026-06-11 18:01:07.056348359 +0900
@@ -41,7 +41,14 @@
             "Run as browser messaging host"
         )
 
-        GLib.unix_signal_add(GLib.PRIORITY_DEFAULT, signal.SIGINT, self.on_sigint, None)
+        try:
+            GLib.unix_signal_add(GLib.PRIORITY_DEFAULT, signal.SIGINT, self.on_sigint, None)
+        except AttributeError:
+            # GLib >= 2.80 moved Unix-specific API to the GLibUnix namespace
+            import gi
+            gi.require_version('GLibUnix', '2.0')
+            from gi.repository import GLibUnix
+            GLibUnix.signal_add(GLib.PRIORITY_DEFAULT, signal.SIGINT, self.on_sigint, None)
 
         self._stdin: GLib.IOChannel = GLib.IOChannel.unix_new(sys.stdin.fileno())
         self._stdin.set_encoding(None)
